description:
&lt;p&gt;** Fixed term contract for 4 years - Apprenticeship. **&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from individuals wishing to become a Management Apprentice and gain experience in the NHS. You will develop new skills and knowledge whilst working with an established team gaining valuable work experience and a recognised apprenticeship qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be enrolled with Anglia Ruskin University and will be required to complete your Chartered Management Degree Apprenticeship within the duration of the placement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to work in an organisation, which enables you to positively impact patient care?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you seeking a well-defined career path with the opportunity to be a future leader of the NHS?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking to build a career in operational management whilst studying towards a Chartered Management Degree Apprenticeship?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the above excites you, then the Clinical Support Services Division at the Norfolk and Norwich University Hospital (NNUH) would like to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical Support Serves Division is currently recruiting a Trainee Operational Manager to work alongside the highly motivated Operational Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is the first of its type the NNUH has seen and will involve supporting the delivery of operational performance targets including waiting lists, finance and to continually improve the quality of services to patients by using best practice standards within the available income.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An enthusiastic individual who is keen to learn every element of operational management by embedding themselves in all functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A team player who is at ease in building relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A determined, capable individual with the ability to work collaboratively to the collective goal of improving patient care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A self-motivated individual who will actively seek learning opportunities from all scenarios&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An individual with strong organisational skills with the ability to prioritise key tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You need to have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education to A-Level standard/Level 3 Apprenticeship&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maths and English at GCSE/Level 2&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Core PRIDE (people-focused, respect, integrity, dedication, excellence) attributes which are central to the NNUH culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to communicate effectively within multidisciplinary teams, both verbally and written&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What will be rewarded:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Charted Management Degree Apprenticeship alongside building unbeatable NHS experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4 year pay progression structure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;20% of time allocated to study&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eligibility Criteria:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All applicants must be:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aged 16+&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resident in the UK/EEA for the last three years&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must not have a Degree, Level 4 qualification or above in a similar subject area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must NOT be in any form of formal government-funded education&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications and Skills Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4 GCSE’s at Grade C /4 or above (or equivalent)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 2 A levels or equivalent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good standard of literacy and numeracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good IT skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time:&lt;/strong&gt; 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Open for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 3rd November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Close for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMatt GoshawkAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel:&lt;/strong&gt; 01603 647402 or 01603 647311&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Emails:&lt;/strong&gt;Matthew.goshawk@nnuh.nhs.uk or Michelle.pelling@nnuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
